"title": "5530: sifting",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5530: sifting",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The process of separating different substances, especially grain and chaff, normally by passing them through sieves. It is used as a symbol of judgment in which the good are separated from the evil.</p>\n<h2>Sifting as an act of separation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:4\">JDG 7:4</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Sifting as a symbol of judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:28\">ISA 30:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:9\">AMO 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:31\">LUK 22:31</a></p>",
